# RISC-V zkVM Track

* *Verifying autoprecompiles*. Intended to support the verification of Powdr Labs' autoprecompiles. Awarded to: Powdr Labs GmbH, Certora. Period: Q4 2025.
* *AVAZAR: Automatic verification tools for zkVM arithmetization*. Intended to support work on automated verification tools for zkVM arithmetizations. Awarded to: Universidad Complutense de Madrid (Albert Rubio). Period: Q4 2025.
* *ZKVM Agnostic Fuzzing*. Intended to support the development of fuzzing techniques applicable to any RISC-V zkVM. Awarded to: zksecurity. Period: Q3 2025.
* *zkBugs 2.0*. Intended to support an update of [zkBugs](https://bugs.zksecurity.xyz). Awarded to: zksecurity. Period: Q3 2025.
* *Automated Verification of ZK Circuits*. Intended to support the development of techniques to automatically verify the consistency between witness generation and constraints. Awarded to: Veridise. Period: Q3 2025.
* *ZKarnage: Stress Testing ZK Systems Through Maximum Pain*. Intended to support work on prover killers. Awarded to: Conner Swann. Period: Q2 2025.
* *Plonky3 in Rocq*. Intended to support an integration of Plonky3 with Rocq. Awarded to: Formal Land. Period: Q2 2025.
* *Plonky3 to Lean*. Intended to support an integration of Plonky3 with Lean. Awarded to: Nethermind. Period: Q1 2025.
* *Evaluating Verus for circuits and EVM precompiles*. Intended to support an evaluation of Verus as a tool to verify representative Rust code. Awarded to: CertiK. Period: Q1 2025.
* *Better Rocq tactics for modular arithmetic & handling packed integers*. Intended to support the development of Rocq tactics for handing arithmetic modulo and for handling packed integers. Awarded to: CertiK. Period: Q1 2025.
* *cLean*. Intended to support the development of [cLean](https://github.com/Verified-zkEVM/clean), a Lean DSL aimed at writing AIR circuits directly in Lean (rather than verifying pre-existing circuits extracted to Lean). Awarded to: zkSecurity. Period: Q4 2025.
* *LLZK*. Intended to support for the development LLZK, a family of MLIR dialects for circuits. Awarded to: Veridise. Period: Q4 2024, Q4 2025.
* *Lean backend for Sail*. Intended to support the development of a Lean backend for Sail (adding to the existing HOL4, Isabelle, and Rocq backends) that will allow the extraction of the official RISC-V Sail specification to Lean. Awarded to: University of Cambridge, Galois, Lindy Labs (first grant only). Period: Q1 2025, Q3 2025.
* *zkLean*. Intended to support an effort to develop zKLean, a Lean DSL for constraints, as well as integration of zkLean with LLZK. Awarded to: Galois. Period: Q1 2025, Q3 2025.

# EVM Track

* *Certified compilation*. Intended to support research aiming to establish methods for certified compilation in the Rocq ecosystem together with tools for high assurance cryptography. Awarded to: Aarhus University. Period: Q4 2024.
* *Development of an EVM in Rocq*. Intended to support the development of a canonical, maintainable, and validated EVM specification in Rocq that can be the basis for a verified implementation of the EVM specification for RISC-V via certified compilation. Awarded to: KTH Royal Institute of Technology. Period: Q4 2024.
* *Verification of revm and Lean backend for K*. Intended to support (i) effort to verify the correctness of revm compiled to RISC-V against KEVM (a EVM specification in K); (ii) the development of a Lean backend for K that will make it possible to compare KEVM to a Lean specification of the EVM, and open up possibilities to use the K tooling for language semantics in Lean in future work. Awarded to: Runtime Verification. Period: Q4 2024.

# Cryptography Track

* *Technical Review of Fiat-Shamir From Duplex Sponges*. Intended to support a thorough technical review of the Fiat-Shamir transformation instantiated via duplex sponges. Awarded to: University of Maryland (Kasra Abbaszadeh). Period: Q4 2025.
* *Rust Verification Through Lean 4 Tooling*. Intended to support a three month investigation into Lean 4 based formal verification of Rust components used in zkEVM and zkVM stacks, focused on using the hax toolchain. Awarded to: Runtime Verification. Period: Q4 2025.
* *STIR & WHIR constructions in ArkLib*. Intended to support the addition of executable specifications for STIR and WHIR in ArkLib. Awarded to: Nethermind. Period: Q4 2025.
* *Fiat-Shamir specification*. Intended to support the development of a specification of the Fiat-Shamir transformation based on duplex sponges. Awarded to: Article 12, LLC (Michele Orrù). Period: Q4 2025.
* *Bluebell*. Intended to support the implementation of the Bluebell program logic in Lean for use in ArkLib. Awarded to: Nethermind. Period: Q3 2025.
* *AI proofs in ArkLib*. This grant is intended to support an experiment in using Logical Intelligence's AI tools for proofs in ArkLib. Awarded to: Logical Intelligence. Period: Q3 2025.
* *Binius in ArkLib*. Intended to support the formalization of Binius in ArkLib. Awarded to: Chung Thai Nguyen.
* *Blueprint STIR and WHIR in ArkLib*. Intended to support the development of a blueprint for STIR and WHIR's security theorems in ArkLib. Awarded to: Least Authority. Period: Q1 2025.
* *Blueprint for FRI & Coding Theory prerequisites in ArkLib*. Intended to support the development of a blueprint for FRI and coding theory prerequisites in ArkLib. Awarded to: Nethermind. Period: Q1 2025.
* *ArkLib*. Intended to support the development of [ArkLib](https://github.com/Verified-zkEVM/ArkLib), a library of formalized proof systems in Lean, accompanied by work on [VCVio](https://github.com/Verified-zkEVM/VCV-io). Awarded to: Quang Dao, Devon Tuma, zkSecurity. Period: Q4 2024.

# General Tooling

* *MLIR sidekick for Lean*. Intended to support Lean-MLIR infrastructure development, including fast datastructures and a RISC-V dialect in Lean. Awarded to: University of Cambridge. Period: Q3 2025.
* *Lean backend for hax*. Intended to support the development of a Lean backend for [hax](https://github.com/cryspen/hax). Awarded to: Cryspen. Period: Q2 2025, Q4 2025.

# Events

* *HACS 2026*. Intended to support to [HACS 2026](https://www.hacs-workshop.org/data/HACS_2026_Overview.pdf) in March 2026. Awarded to: Aspiration. Period: Q1 2026.
* *HACS 2025*. Intended to support to [HACS 2025](https://www.hacs-workshop.org/data/HACS_2025_Overview.pdf) in March 2025. Awarded to: Aspiration. Period: Q1 2025.
* *ZKProofs 7*. Intended to support to [ZKProofs 7](https://zkproof.org/events/zkproof-7-sofia) in March 2025. Awarded to: ZKProofs. Period: Q1 2025.
* *ZKProofs Zurich Event*. Intended to support to host a small one day event in Zurich in October 2024 to discuss the formal verification of proof systems. A summary of the event is available [here](https://zkproof.org/verifier). Awarded to: ZKProofs. Period: Q4 2024.

# Community Resources and Education

* *Foundations of Probabilistic Proofs MOOC*. Intended to support the development of a MOOC on the foundations of probabilistic proofs. Awarded to: Algorithmic Security GmbH (Alessandro Chiesa). Period: Q3 2025.
* *EthProofs*. Intended to support the continued development of ethproofs.org following initial work by the Ethereum Digital Studio team. Awarded to: Fara Woolf. Period: Q2 2025, Q3 2025.
